 {"id":"bd-pgs-epic","title":"PORT: pwd/grp/shadow line serializers (putpwent/putgrent/putspent) to core","description":"Lift the format!()-with-from_utf8_unchecked line serialization out of putpwent (glibc_internal_abi.rs:5685, ~40 lines), putgrent (glibc_internal_abi.rs:5619, ~35 lines), and putspent (unistd_abi.rs:13366, ~37 lines) into pure-safe core::{pwd,grp} formatters operating on byte slices. Each writes one colon-separated record terminated with newline. The C-ABI marshalling — *const libc::passwd/group/spwd field reads, fwrite at the boundary — stays at the boundary.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T09:33:20.372874Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T09:37:21.475889Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T09:37:21.475889Z","close_reason":"Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~110 lines of from_utf8_unchecked + format!() macro code in glibc_internal_abi.rs/unistd_abi.rs replaced by ~50 lines of marshalling over 3 pure-safe Rust formatters in core::{pwd, grp, pwd::shadow}. As a side benefit, putspent now correctly emits the -1 sentinel as empty (matching glibc) — the previous impl wrote the literal \"-1\".","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-piab","title":"syscall: sched_setaffinity invalid pid with valid mask should return ESRCH exactly","description":"Host glibc returns ESRCH for sched_setaffinity(-1, sizeof(cpu_set_t), &mask). Add focused ABI regression coverage so the invalid-pid contract is explicit.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:08:34.217116113Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-22T02:51:19.900178029Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T02:51:19.897958477Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-pjego","title":"PORT: strmode (BSD mode-bit-to-ls-style-string)","description":"BSD strmode(mode_t mode, char *buf) writes 11 ASCII chars + NUL into buf describing the file mode in ls -l format: file type (\"d\",\"l\",\"-\",\"c\",\"b\",\"p\",\"s\",\"w\",\"D\"), then 9 permission chars (rwx triples for owner/group/other) with setuid/setgid/sticky bit overlays (\"s\",\"S\",\"t\",\"T\"). Used by ls(1) implementations and any tool that wants to render mode bits human-readably. Currently missing from frankenlibc-abi/string_abi.rs. Ship as: pure-safe core::stat::strmode helper that returns a [u8; 11] (no NUL — caller writes the trailing NUL into a 12-byte buffer per BSD spec) + abi shim that copies the 11 bytes + NUL into the caller buffer.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T15:04:41.028852041Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T15:09:39.327642794Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T15:09:39.325721700Z","close_reason":"shipped: core::stat::strmode_bytes + string_abi::strmode; new core stat module; 28+8 tests; clippy-clean","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
